Session: sem-equiv-and-paren-fix (2026-04-03)
Agent: Cam

## What was done

1. Built `codex sem-equiv` command in Codex.Cli (Program.SemEquiv.cs).
   Parses stage0/stage1, de-mangles scoped names, matches per module,
   compares normalized bodies. `--show <name>` for per-def investigation.

2. Fixed precedence paren dropping in CodexEmitter.codex. Split
   wrap-binary-child into wrap-binary-left (<) and wrap-binary-right
   (<=, with associativity check). `a - (b + c)` no longer emits as
   `a - b + c`.

3. Added brace-escape normalization to sem-equiv (\{ == {, parser
   treats \{ as passthrough escape so info is lost in IR).

Feature branch `feat/sem-equiv-checker` under review. 3 commits.

